Japan Carbon Emissions Will Rise 10% Without Atomic Power, Yomiuri Says

-- B y   C h i s a k i   W a t a n a b e
-- 
2011-04-20T08:45:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-20/japan-carbon-emissions-will-rise-10-without-atomic-power-yomiuri-says.html
Japan ’s greenhouse gas emissions
would increase 10 percent if the nation doesn’t add new nuclear
reactors and restart the ones damaged by the March 11
earthquake,  Yomiuri newspaper  reported, citing an estimate by
the  Environment Ministry .  The estimate reflects emissions levels in 2020 compared
with the 1990 baseline, the paper reported. Japan has been
planning to build nine new reactors. It has 14 that went out of
service when the quake struck.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Chisaki Watanabe in Tokyo at 
 cwatanabe5@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Reed Landberg at 
 landberg@bloomberg.net  